channel.title: DTO
channel.description: This is a randomly ordered feed of the most recent entries from DTO, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Shutdown fallout: Energy Dept. axes billions for green projects in blue states
item.description: The Energy Department's cancellations of projects directly affected 16 states won by Kamala Harris in the 2024 presidential election.

item.title: Economic calendar: Not all of today’s data is on pause during the shutdown
Trump admin freezes $2.1 billion for Chicago projects, blames Democrats for shutdown holdup
item.description: The move came on the third day of the federal government shutdown, which President Donald Trump has blamed on Democrats in Congress.

item.title: Market bubbles burst only when central banks tighten: B. of A.’s top strategist
Trump touts shutdown as 'unprecedented opportunity' to cut more Democratic priorities
item.description: Trump in a Truth Social post said he will meet with Office of Management and Budget Director Russell Vought to discuss cutting agencies.

item.title: Apple removes ICE tracking apps after Trump AG pressure
item.description: Joshua Aaron has said he created ICEBlock after seeing the Trump administration's deportation efforts, which he said evoked events in Nazi Germany.

item.title: Stocks struggle to put six-session win streaks on the scoreboard — live coverage
U.S. stock futures indicate further records ahead for major indices
U.S. job market contracted for a fourth straight month in September: ISM
Anduril and Palantir battlefield communication system has deep flaws, Army memo says
item.description: Anduril and Palantir battlefield communication system has high-risk security problems according to a recent internal Army memo.
